“Sometimes we see things that [our customers] can’t even articulate. But it isn’t about our customers telling us what they want. It’s about us understanding enough of what they’re trying to accomplish so we can come up with something better.”

Barbara Hulit

SVP


Joined the Fortive family in
2005









Accelerating Progress
Fortive is a global family of more than 20 industry-leading companies, united by a shared purpose: essential technology for the people who accelerate progress. From transportation and precision automation to breakthrough consumer experiences, we take on big challenges with real impact.



 


 





Teletrac Navman helped Domino’s Pizza enhance its mobile app with Global Positioning System (GPS) tracking capability. Customers can track their pizza from creation to delivery, and Domino’s benefits from improved operational efficiency and safety. 






We know the only way to achieve our shared purpose is through our people—great people equipped with proven tools and an environment that enables them to seize opportunities, imagine the next breakthrough and create the next innovation.





A Community that Cares

 
 


“We’ve hosted students here on campus, who come and learn about engineering. I always see students’ eyes light up. We actually sort of had to kick them out at the end of the class.”

Graham McCarthy


Tektronix


Joined the Fortive family in
2004










 



The culture of giving at Tektronix is a source of pride and joy for its employees. The Tektronix Foundation supports a number of community charities, including Susan G Komen Race for the Cure and STEM classes for youth. Employees are allotted paid time each quarter for volunteer work, and many extend their volunteer commitments to their own time as well. Fortive companies have a culture of caring, which benefits employees as well as those they help.









Join our Extraordinary Team
Fortive is a place where exceptional people work. Fortive offers opportunities at all levels in a wide range of departments including human resources, engineering, marketing, sales and finance at its corporate headquarters in Everett, Washington and throughout its family of operating companies worldwide.
We are proud to offer you and your family a variety of benefits—it’s a key aspect of what makes our company a great place to work. Your particular benefits package will depend on your position, location and years with the company. Here’s a look at what you might be eligible for.
Health insurance
