Fortive Corporation Key Developments

Fortive Corporation Announces Unaudited Consolidated Earnings Results for the Second Quarter and Six Months Ended June 30, 2017; Provides Earnings Guidance for the Third Quarter and Full Year of 2017
Jul 27 17
Fortive Corporation announced unaudited consolidated earnings results for the second quarter and six months ended June 30, 2017. For the quarter, the company reported sales o $1,628.8 million against $1,555.1 million a year ago. Operating profit was $348.3 million against $322.1 million a year ago. Earnings before income taxes were $325.6 million against $319.4 million a year ago. Net earnings were $240.1 million against $238.9 million a year ago. Diluted net earnings per share were $0.68 against $0.69 a year ago. Adjusted net earnings (Non-GAAP) were $249.9 million against $220.8 million a year ago. Adjusted diluted net earnings per share (Non-GAAP) were $0.71 million against $0.64 million a year ago. 

 For the six months, the company reported sales was $3,164 million against $3,029.8 million a year ago. Operating profit was $643.2 million against $585.1 million a year ago. Earnings before income taxes were $597.9 million against $582.4 million a year ago. Net earnings were $439.8 million against $420.9 million a year ago. Diluted net earnings per share were $1.25 against $1.22 a year ago. Adjusted net earnings (Non-GAAP) were $459.3 million against $402.7 million a year ago. Adjusted diluted net earnings per share (Non-GAAP) were $1.31 million against $1.17 million a year ago.

The company provides earnings guidance for the third quarter and full year of 2017. For the quarter ending September 29, 2017, the company expected diluted net earnings per share to be in the range $0.66-$0.70 and adjusted diluted net earnings per share to be in the range $0.69-$0.73.

For the year ending December 31, 2017, the company expected diluted net earnings per share to be in the range $2.61-$2.69 and adjusted diluted net earnings per share to be in the range $2.72-$2.80.


