Fortive: Essential technology for the people who accelerate progress.
A Fortune 500 startup? That’s Fortive. We’re based in Everett, Washington, but our impact circles the globe through our family of more than 20 companies. These companies didn’t come together by accident. Each one is a market leader in its industry. Each one helps make the world stronger, safer and better.
We work together to make progress where it’s needed the most, accelerating breakthrough innovation in fast-moving fields like software development, robotics, transportation, energy and healthcare. We are united by a shared purpose and values and by our commitment to making an impact on the world. At Fortive you can work with and learn from great people, in a vibrant culture defined by opportunity, empowerment and continuous learning and growth. We are a set of extraordinary teams, working together to achieve extraordinary things.
We are Fortive.








Our Shared Purpose



 






 

Our Innovation
It’s not every day that your company can say “This is an industry first,” but Tektronix’ new 5 Series MSO redefines oscilloscopes with 5 industry first innovations, delivering unprecedented flexibility and unmatched visibility into complex embedded systems. This is the first product in a series of introductions, as part of our platform developed with the new Tek049 chip. Congratulations to everyone for all the hard work on bringing this product to market. This is world class innovation, and Tektronix is leading the way!

Learn More








Fortive Operating Companies


Fortive's portfolio of businesses spans the globe, and their innovations surround each of us daily in the form of essential technology. They keep power grids and factories running, support the largest data centers, advance robotics through precision motion and automation, and drive the global economy by ensuring safe, efficient transport of goods. Each of our operating companies is working to accelerate breakthrough innovation in its field.




 


Fluke is the world leader in the manufacture, distribution and service of electronic test tools, biomedical equipment and networking solutions.



 


Kollmorgen designs and manufactures motion systems and components for a wide variety of industries worldwide.



 


Thomson is a world leader in precision mechanical motion technology.



 


Portescap designs and manufactures precise, compact motors for use in the medical and aerospace industries.



 


Dynapar offers the world's broadest range of encoders, resolvers and accessories for motion feedback control.



 


Jacobs Vehicle Systems is a leader in engine braking technology, trusted by the world's most well-known engine manufacturers.



 


Matco Tools is a manufacturer and distributor of quality professional automotive repair tools and diagnostic equipment.



 


Hennessy Industries manufactures wheel-service equipment for the automotive industry, with its Ammco, Coats, Baseline and Bada brands.



 


West Control Solutions is an industry-leading manufacturer of temperature control, process control, and automation products.



 


At Qualitrol we are redefining condition based monitoring technology for Electric utilities assets.



 


Gilbarco Veeder-Root supplies fuel dispensers and point-of-sale technology for convenience stores and gas stations.



 


Tektronix designs and manufactures test and measurement equipment, accelerating global innovation in industries such as communications, health, and aerospace.



 


Invetech helps companies bring new products to market with its product realization and automation consulting services.



 


Pacific Scientific is an engineering company providing mission-critical solutions for the aerospace and defense industries.



 


Gems Sensors & Controls is a global manufacturer of customized sensors, switches, controls and valves.



 


Setra Systems designs and manufactures an array of electronic instruments that measure pressure, acceleration and weight.



 


Anderson-Negele provides hygienic instrumentation sensors for the food and life sciences industries.



 


Teletrac Navman provides cloud-based GPS fleet-tracking software for the trucking industry.




